{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 11:32:55.387268", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting diagnosis report — SDN spine–leaf lab\\nTimestamp: (current run)\\n\\nSummary\\n- Anomaly detected: End-hosts in the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet cannot reach each other (100% packet loss; ICMP returns \"Destination Host Unreachable\").\\n- Fault localization: All three OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) show the Open vSwitch service inactive. The forwarding plane on those switches is not running.\\n- Root cause (most likely): Open vSwitch daemons on the switches are stopped/inactive → no L2 forwarding/bridging between host-facing ports and spine/leaf ports. This prevents host-to-host connectivity in 10.0.0.0/24 even though host IPs and switch management IPs exist.\\n\\nObserved symptoms (high level)\\n- Host-to-host pings fail immediately with \"Destination Host Unreachable\" (100% loss).\\n- Hosts are configured with correct 10.0.0.x/24 addresses, but see no incoming traffic.\\n- Switch interfaces show they are present, but the OVS bridge(s) are down and openvswitch service is inactive.\\n\\nKey evidence (extracted from collected outputs)\\n1) Host addressing (all hosts present and have expected addresses)\\n- host_1_1: eth0 10.0.0.1/24\\n- host_1_2: eth0 10.0.0.2/24\\n- host_2_1: eth0 10.0.0.3/24\\n- host_2_2: eth0 10.0.0.4/24\\n\\n2) Ping failures between hosts (examples)\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2:\\n  \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\"\\n  3 transmitted, 0 received, 100% packet loss\\n- host_1_1 -> host_2_1 / host_2_2: same \"Destination Host Unreachable\", 100% loss\\n- host_2_2 -> host_1_2: same symptom\\n\\n3) Open vSwitch service status on switches\\n- leaf_1: openvswitch-switch.service ... Active: inactive (dead)\\n- leaf_2: openvswitch-switch.service ... Active: inactive (dead)\\n- spine_1: openvswitch-switch.service ... Active: inactive (dead)\\n\\n4) Switch interface state vs bridge state (example)\\n- leaf_1:\\n  - physical ports (eth0/eth1/eth2/eth3) show UP and some RX/TX counters exist\\n  - logical bridge interfaces (ovs-system, leaf_1) show state DOWN\\n  - leaf_1 has management IP: eth3 inet 20.0.0.2/24 (interface is up)\\n- spine_1: eth2 has inet 20.0.0.1/24 (up)\\n- leaf_2: eth3 inet 20.0.0.3/24 (up)\\n\\nInterpretation / root-cause reasoning\\n- Hosts are correctly configured on 10.0.0.0/24 but see no path to each other; pings fail with \"Destination Host Unreachable\" originating at the source host, indicating the host stack cannot find a direct L2 path to the destination (ARP resolution failing or local gateway unreachable).\\n- The OVS daemons that provide switching/bridging and OpenFlow connectivity are inactive on all three switch nodes. Even though some NICs show UP and management IPs are present, the OVS bridge(s) are not running, so frames arriving at the host-facing ports are not being forwarded between ports/links.\\n- Because the data-plane switching is down on leaf and spine switches, intra-subnet host forwarding is broken — this explains the observed 100% packet loss between hosts on 10.0.0.0/24.\\n- The presence of management IPs on eth3 for switches suggests control-plane/management network interfaces are up, but the core problem is the switching daemon\\'s absence — therefore the controller (20.0.0.100) may be reachable on the management plane, but it cannot control a non-running OVS service.\\n\\nImpact\\n- All inter-host traffic on 10.0.0.0/24 is impacted — no L2 forwarding.\\n- Any SDN/OpenFlow-dependent flows across the spine–leaf fabric are non-functional while OVS is down.\\n- Management reachability (20.0.0.0/24) appears present on interfaces, but forwarding for data-plane hosts is disrupted.\\n\\nAdditional observations / notes\\n- Host packet counters: hosts show small TX counts but zero RX, consistent with attempts to send ARP/ICMP and receive no replies.\\n- Switch physical interfaces show RX counters but no TX or bridged forwarding (bridges are down), consistent with received frames that are not being forwarded by an active OVS instance.\\n- No direct evidence was collected about the controller\\'s status or connectivity to 20.0.0.100; management interfaces are configured on switches so controller reachability is a separate check.\\n\\nRecommended next data to collect (diagnostic only — no remediation)\\n- Confirm controller (20.0.0.100) reachability from switches (ping/traceroute) and check controller logs to see whether it reports switch connections.\\n- Check system logs (journalctl or /var/log/openvswitch) on leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 for why openvswitch-switch.service is inactive (crash, failed start, config error).\\n- Capture output of ovs-vsctl show and ps /var/run/openvswitch* to confirm process/bridge state once service status is inspected in logs.\\n- Check for recent administrative actions (was OVS intentionally stopped?), package updates, or resource exhaustion that may have stopped the service.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- There is a clear L2 connectivity failure affecting host-to-host communication. Root cause is localized to the switches: Open vSwitch daemons on leaf_1, leaf_2 and spine_1 are inactive, preventing packet forwarding across the fabric.\\n\\nIf you want, I can (upon request) collect the suggested additional diagnostic logs/commands (controller reachability check, switch journal logs, ovs-vsctl output) to further confirm cause., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c8427718-e09c-4bc4-b535-13913c2fd8af'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5-mini", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
